## Architecture Overview

The backend follows a **modular DDD architecture** with NestJS:

```
src/
├── modules/          # Feature modules (controller, service, DTOs per feature)
├── domain/           # Domain entities, value objects, repository interfaces
├── infrastructure/   # DynamoDB repositories, external adapters, AWS SDK clients
├── common/           # Shared filters, guards, interceptors, pipes, decorators
└── config/           # Configuration module and typed config schema
```

**Dependency rule**: outer layers depend on inner layers. Domain has zero dependencies on infrastructure or NestJS.

```
controllers → services → domain ← repositories
```

