## DTOs and Validation

DTOs use `class-validator` decorators. The global `ValidationPipe` handles transformation and validation automatically.

```typescript
// src/modules/foo/dto/create-foo.dto.ts
import { IsString, IsNotEmpty, MaxLength } from 'class-validator';

export class CreateFooDto {
  @IsString()
  @IsNotEmpty()
  @MaxLength(100)
  name!: string;
}
```

```typescript
// src/modules/foo/dto/foo-response.dto.ts
export class FooResponseDto {
  id!: string;
  name!: string;
  createdAt!: string;
}
```

**Rules:**
- DTOs must be **classes** (not interfaces) so `class-transformer` can instantiate them
- Use `class-validator` decorators for all input DTO properties
- Separate request DTOs (`CreateFooDto`) from response DTOs (`FooResponseDto`)
- Never return domain entities directly — always map to a response DTO

