## DynamoDB Patterns

### Single-Table Design

All entities share one table. Use composite keys to separate entity types:

| Entity | PK | SK |
|---|---|---|
| User | `USER#<id>` | `USER#<id>` |
| Order | `ORDER#<id>` | `ORDER#<id>` |
| Order by User | `USER#<userId>` | `ORDER#<orderId>` |

Always include an `entityType` attribute for filtering.

### Key Rules

- Use `PK` and `SK` as partition and sort key attribute names
- Prefix keys with entity type in uppercase (`USER#`, `ORDER#`)
- Add a GSI when you need to query by a non-primary attribute
- Never hardcode table names — always read from `ConfigService`
- Always use AWS SDK v3 (`@aws-sdk/client-dynamodb` + `@aws-sdk/lib-dynamodb`)
- Use `DynamoDBDocumentClient` to work with plain JavaScript objects

